Kikka-kakkoset:

1. Prefer RequestAnimationFrame() instead of SetInterval()
   https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/window/requestAnimationFrame
   SetInterval can be used in more specific cases to gain more control over the framerate:
   https://www.w3schools.com/jsref/met_win_setinterval.asp

2. Event Listener works mainly on default DOM elements (div, button, canvas, footer..). If you need to listen to instantiated objects (firstbutton.addEventListener('resize', () =>
   console.log(firstbutton.width, firstbutton.height));) put it inside updateGame loop. Otherwise it will only log the message once.
3. Can't use a function or variable from game.js in index.html (check case drawBackgroundImage). Add "window.drawBackgroundImage = drawBackgroundImage" to the same file where the function has been declared. This makes it global.

