vscode.dev-link on kätevä: kirjoita TODO:, FIXME: tms. > oik. hiiri > share > pastea linkki minne vaan koodia. Linkki avautuu browserissa.

By default, clicking on a vscode.dev-link will open the browser version of Visual Studio Code (VSCode) and navigate to the specific line of code.
However, if you prefer to open the link in the VSCode application itself, you can follow these steps:

1. Copy the vscode.dev-link URL by right-clicking on the link and selecting "Copy link address" or a similar option.
2. Open the VSCode application on your computer.
3. In the VSCode menu, go to "File" > "Add Folder to Workspace" or use the keyboard shortcut Ctrl+K Ctrl+O (Cmd+K Cmd+O on macOS).
4. Choose a folder on your computer to add to the workspace. This step is necessary to enable the option to open external links in the VSCode application.
5. Once the folder is added to the workspace, go to "File" > "Open Folder" or use the keyboard shortcut Ctrl+K Ctrl+O (Cmd+K Cmd+O on macOS).
6. In the file explorer, navigate to the folder where the file corresponding to the vscode.dev-link URL is located.
7. Open the file that contains the line referenced by the vscode.dev-link.
8. In the file, go to the line referenced by the vscode.dev-link.
9. Now, you can click on the vscode.dev-link URL, and it should open the link in the VSCode application itself, taking you to the specific line of code.
